From 17631d3fd166140254701a8d5096edebf49a0183 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ekane bryan <ekanebryan5@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 06:42:31 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf(cache): Redis caching for public reads + fix bookmark
 toast delay
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Backend caching (Redis via CACHE_STORE=redis):
- Categories: cached 1h, flushed on admin create/update/delete.
- Regions/cities/divisions: cached 1h (common no-filter path),
  flushed on destroy.
- Events list: cached 60s keyed by params (public only, admin bypasses).
  Stores JSON response in Redis for ~1ms reads instead of ~50-200ms queries.
- All cache reads wrapped in try/catch — falls back to DB if Redis is down.

Frontend fix:
- useBookmarks: removed blocking fetchBookmarks() after API call.
  The toast now appears immediately after the bookmark API resolves
  (~200ms) instead of waiting for a full re-fetch (~1-2s). The optimistic
  state update + background dispatch keep the UI in sync.
